    <refsection id="Description_Switch">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This is a non-ideal two-pole switch. If the explicit input become positive, two pins are connected via a resistor of resistance RON). Otherwise, two pins are connected via ROFF resistance.
        </para>
        <para>
            <note>
                Note that using this block may result in a stiff model, so try to choose proper error tolerances.
            </note>
        </para>
        <para>
        </para>
    </refsection>
